“books” includes any register or other record of information and 
any accounts or accounting records, however compiled, recorded 
or  stored,  and  also  includes  any  document;

“management  entity”  means  the  corporation  authorized  by  the 
minister  to  act  on  behalf  of  a  langkawi  company  or  foreign 
langkawi  company  under  section  0  of  this act;

“issued  share  capital”,  in  relation  to  par  value  shares,  means, 
at  any  particular  time,  the  sum  of  the  par  value  of  all  shares  of 
a  langkawi  company  that  have  been  issued;

“expert”  means  an  engineer,  valuer,  accountant,  auditor  and 
any  other  person  whose  profession  or  reputation  gives  authority 
to  a  statement  made  by  him;

“Registrar” means the Registrar of Companies under the Companies 
act 965 [Act 125], and includes any Regional Registrar, deputy 
Registrar  or assistant  Registrar  of  Companies;

“annual fee payment date” means the date on which the annual fee 
of  a  langkawi  company  shall  be  payable  pursuant  to  subsection 
(6);

(a)  any  shares  held  or  power  exercisable  by  that  other 
corporation  in  a  trustee  or  fiduciary  capacity  shall  be 
treated  as  not  held  or  exercisable  by  it;

(e)  it  acquires  or  holds  any  lease  of  any  property  for  the 
purposes  of  its  operation  or  as  accommodation  for  its 
officers  or  employees;

(b)  contains  matter  that,  in  a  material  particular,  is  false 
or  misleading  in  the  form  or  context  in  which  it  is 
included;

(i)  any  return  of  allotment  of  shares  for  cash  which 
has  been  lodged  or  filed  for  not  less  than  six 
years;

(c)  the amount of the share capital with which it is proposed 
to  be  registered  and  the  division  thereof  into  shares  of 
a  fixed  amount;

(a)  make  arrangements,  on  the  issue  of  shares,  for  varying 
the  amounts  and  times  of  payment  of  calls  as  between 
shareholders;

(i)  in  the  case  of  goods,  when  the  ownership  or 
property  therein  passes  to  the  company  or  when 
they  are  delivered  to  it;

(d)  converting  all  or  any  of  its  paid-up  shares  into  stock 
and  reconverting  that  stock  into  paid-up  shares  of  any 
denomination;

(ii)  is an agreement, or is within a class of agreements, 
prescribed by regulations for the purposes of this 
paragraph;

(b)  the  address  of  the  registered  office  of  the  company  in 
langkawi or, where the certificate is issued by a branch 
of  the  company,  the  address  of  that  branch;

(a)  uses  or  authorizes  the  use  of  any  seal  purporting  to  be 
a  seal  of  the  company  whereon  its  name  does  not  so 
appear;

(a)  if two or more persons hold shares jointly, each of them 
may  be  present  in  person  or  by  proxy  at  a  meeting  of 
members  and  may  speak  as  a  member;

(a)  the total number of the shares of the members entitled to 
vote on all the matters to be considered at the meeting; 
or

(c)  the date at which any person who ceased to be a member 
during the previous seven years so ceased to be a member; 
and

(b)  determine whether approval of the proposed arrangement 
by  any  person  should  be  obtained  and  the  manner  of 
obtaining  the  approval;

(a)  a certified copy of the certificate of its incorporation or 
registration  in  its  place  of  incorporation  or  origin,  or  a 
document  of  similar  effect;

(b)  a certified copy of its charter, statute or memorandum and 
articles  of  association  or  other  instrument  constituting 
or  defining  its  constitution;

(a)  the charter, statute, memorandum or articles of association 
of  a  foreign  langkawi  company,  or  other  instrument 
relating  to  the  company,  lodged  with  the  Registrar;

(a)  has contravened the provisions of any terms, conditions, 
restrictions or limitations as specified in the authorization; 
or

(i)  where  the  company  has  a  share  capital,  by  the 
holders of not less than three fourths of the shares 
of  each  class;

(ii)  by  the  holders  of  not  less  than  three-fourths  of 
the  company’s  debentures  (if  any)  of  each  class; 
and

(a)  commence any legal proceedings, carry on any business 
or  in  any  way  deal  with  the  assets  of  the  langkawi 
company;

(b)  defend  any  legal  proceedings,  make  any  claim  or  claim 
any right for, or in the name of, the langkawi company; 
